{{Infobox building | name = John A. Delaney Student Union | native_name = | native_name_lang = | former_names = | alternate_names = | status = | image = UNF Student Union pic.jpg | image_alt = | image_size = 200px | caption = | map_type = | map_alt = | map_caption = | altitude = | building_type = [[Student activity center|Student union]] | architectural_style = | structural_system = | cost = | ren_cost = | client = | owner = | current_tenants = | landlord = | location = [[Jacksonville, Florida]], United States | address = | location_town = | location_country = | coordinates = | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = | completion_date = | opened_date = 2009 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | height = | diameter = | antenna_spire = | roof = | top_floor = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = 3 | floor_area = | seating_type = | seating_capacity = | elevator_count = | main_contractor = | architect = | architecture_firm = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | other_designers = | quantity_surveyor = | awards = | designations = | ren_architect = | ren_firm = | ren_str_engineer = | ren_serv_engineer = | ren_civ_engineer = | ren_oth_designers = | ren_qty_surveyor = | ren_awards = | parking = | url = http://www.unf.edu/studentunion | embedded = | references = }}
The '''John A. Delaney Student Union''' is the [[student activity center]] at the [[University of North Florida]] (UNF) in [[Jacksonville, Florida]], U.S. The first such building in UNF's history, it opened in 2009. It is located on the university's campus across from [[UNF Arena]]. The Student Union has been awarded several architectural awards, including the AIA Jacksonville Best Education Building in Florida award (2012), fourth place in AIA Florida's Best Building in Florida in 100 Years rankings (2012), and the AIA Jacksonville Design Award of Merit (2010).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dasherhurst.com/about/awards/|title=Awards {{!}} Dasher Hurst Architects|website=www.dasherhurst.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-18}}</ref> It was named in 2018 for former UNF president [[John Delaney (Florida politician)|John A. Delaney]].<ref name=DuChanois>{{cite news |last= DuChanois|first= Colette |date= April 5, 2018 |title= UNF Student Union named for John Delaney|url= https://www.news4jax.com/news/local/jacksonville/unf-student-union-named-for-john-delaney|work= www.news4jax.com |access-date= June 4, 2018 }}</ref>
==History== Opened in 2009, the Student Union is the first in the university's [[University of North Florida#History|history]]. It succeeds the Robinson Student Life Center as the main recreational facility on campus, but the Robinson Center only included a fraction of the amenities of the current Student Union. Plans for a Student Union go back as far as the 1980s,<ref>http://www.jacksonville.com/tu-online/stories/080608/met_314196107.shtml</ref> but the project was finalized in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unf.edu/view_art.php?article=416 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090530215003/http://www.unf.edu/view_art.php?article=416 |archivedate=2009-05-30 |df= }}</ref> The Student Union is a central part of UNF's 2006 announcement to spend $170 million on new structures on campus including new housing, a College of Education building, and parking.<ref>http://jacksonville.bizjournals.com/jacksonville/stories/2006/12/04/story11.html</ref>
In 2018, the facility was named the John A. Delaney Student Union, after [[John Delaney (Florida politician)|John A. Delaney]]. Delaney, who retired on May 31, 2018, had served as president of the school for 15 years.<ref name=DuChanois/>
==Details== [[Image:UNF student union at night.JPG|left|thumb|250px|Front of Student Union at night]] *The official size of the structure is {{convert|150048|sqft|m2}}. *The facility cost $50.4 million. *The Coxwell Amphitheater has a capacity of 6,000 people. *First Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design (LEED) certified student union in Florida.
==Features== UNF's Student Union consists of two buildings connected by a covered walkway known as Osprey Plaza. The structure includes contains the UNF bookstore, a convenience store, restaurants, a game room, an auditorium, a ballroom, Community First bank branch, an LGBT Resource Center, and an amphitheater. UNF [[Student governments in the United States|student government]] is housed there, as is the Spinnaker Media, which includes UNF's [[student newspaper]] [[The Spinnaker]], Spinnaker Television, and Spinnaker Radio. The Lufrano Intercultural Gallery of Art and other various student organizations like Fraternity and Sorority Life have their offices in the facility.<ref>http://www.unfspinnaker.com/news/2009/04/09/an-in-depth-look-at-the-student-union/</ref> The Boathouse restaurant is the third variant of the UNF tradition. The food court has an Einstein Bros, Panda Express, and Slice Pizzeria.<ref>http://www.dineoncampus.com/unf/?cmd=Menus</ref> Market Days are held each Wednesday from 10am-2pm in Osprey Plaza and features vendors from the region.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unf.edu/studentunion/marketday.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-12-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091010122227/http://www.unf.edu/studentunion/marketday.html |archivedate=2009-10-10 |df= }}</ref>
