'''Roy D. Simon''' is the Howard Lichtenstein Distinguished Professor of Legal Ethics at [[Hofstra University]].<ref>[http://law.hofstra.edu/directory/faculty/fulltimefaculty/ftfac_simon.html Hofstra]</ref>
He was the 2008 [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] nominee for the [[New York State Senate]], running against then-[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] State Senate Majority Leader [[Dean Skelos]]. He currently resides in [[West Hempstead]] and ran to be the [[State Senator]] representing the Ninth District in [[Long Island]]. Some of these communities include the [[Five Towns]], [[Valley Stream]], [[Rockville Centre]], and others. Political pundits acknowledged that it would be difficult to oust [[Dean Skelos]].<ref>[http://thejewishstar.wordpress.com/2008/10/16/republican-dean-skelos-vs-democrat-roy-simon/ Jewish Star]</ref>
==Education== Simon attended [[Williams College]] for his undergraduate degree and [[NYU Law School]] for his JD. He started his academic work as an instructor the [[Washington University in St. Louis]] School of Law.
